WEBVTT

00:01.160 --> 00:02.593
Veronica: PREVIOUSLY
ON "VERONICA MARS"...

00:02.600 --> 00:04.295
IT'S BEEN A YEAR SINCE
LILLY KANE WAS MURDERED.

00:04.300 --> 00:06.564
DAD TOLD JAKE KANE,
THE MOST POWERFUL MAN IN TOWN,

00:06.570 --> 00:09.664
HE WAS SURE HE WAS INVOLVED
IN HIS OWN DAUGHTER'S DEATH.

00:09.670 --> 00:12.275
DUNCAN KANE --
HE USED TO BE MY BOYFRIEND.

00:12.280 --> 00:14.168
AND LET'S NOT FORGET
LOGAN ECHOLLS.

00:14.180 --> 00:16.671
HIS DAD MAKES $20 MILLION
A PICTURE.

00:16.680 --> 00:18.204
SMILE, LOGAN.

00:18.210 --> 00:21.748
DON'T FORGET -- THESE FOLKS
PAY FOR ALL OF THIS.

00:21.750 --> 00:25.208
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING ON OUR BEACH?

00:25.220 --> 00:26.710
AM I SUPPOSED
TO APOLOGIZE?

00:26.720 --> 00:29.018
AM I SUPPOSED TO SHAKE
IN MY BOOTS, WEEVIL?

00:29.020 --> 00:30.419
MAYBE.

00:30.430 --> 00:32.295
LOOK AROUND YOU, MAN.
IT AIN'T 15 ON 4 TONIGHT.

00:32.300 --> 00:34.860
Veronica: ALL THIS TIME,
I'VE BEEN THINKING MOM BOLTED

00:34.860 --> 00:37.522
'CAUSE SHE COULDN'T HANDLE
LOSING EVERYTHING.

00:37.530 --> 00:39.395
MAYBE SHE JUST COULDN'T HANDLE
LOSING ME.

00:39.400 --> 00:42.665
CLARENCE WIEDMAN, A MAN WHO TOOK
SURVEILLANCE PHOTOS OF ME --

00:42.670 --> 00:44.661
THE ONES WITH ME FRAMED
IN A GUNSIGHT.

00:44.670 --> 00:46.501
YOU'VE REACH ED
CLARENCE WIEDMAN,

00:46.510 --> 00:48.375
HEAD OF SECURITY,
KANE SOFI'WARE.

00:48.380 --> 00:51.440
I KNOW WHO'S RESPONSIBLE FOR
SCARING MOM AWAY FROM NEPTUNE --

00:51.450 --> 00:56.342
A FORMER LOVER --
DAD'S NEMESIS, JAKE KANE.

00:56.350 --> 00:58.181
WILL YOU MAKE IT SNOW?

00:58.190 --> 01:00.988
SURE THING,
BUT DON'T GET YOUR HOPES UP.

01:00.990 --> 01:04.357
YOU'LL NEVER GET ANYWHERE
WITH THAT ONE.

01:04.360 --> 01:05.657
WE'LL HAVE TO TRY.

01:05.660 --> 01:08.652
THE DOWNSIDE TO BEING
AN ONLY CHILD --

01:08.660 --> 01:12.790
YOU KNOW ALL THE SCARY
HANDMADE ORNAMENTS ARE YOURS.

01:12.800 --> 01:15.132
THIS CONCERNS ME.

01:18.540 --> 01:20.701
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WAIT.

01:20.710 --> 01:23.838
YOU GOT TO PUT ANOTHER
PADRES ORNAMENT OVER THERE.

01:25.180 --> 01:27.978
WHAT? IT SHOULD BE SPREAD OUT
SO IT'S EVEN.

01:27.980 --> 01:30.778
YOU KNOW, THERE ARE SOME PEOPLE
WHO THINK CHRISTMAS

01:30.790 --> 01:33.088
IS ABOUT THE BIRTH OF CHRIST
AND NOT BASEBALL.

01:33.090 --> 01:36.150
WE'RE ALL ENTITLED
TO OUR OWN RELIGIONS, VERONICA.

01:36.160 --> 01:37.855
WHAT DO YOU WANT
FOR CHRISTMAS?

01:37.860 --> 01:39.589
YOUR LOVE AND RESPECT.

01:39.600 --> 01:42.626
SERIOUSLY, IF YOU COULD HAVE
ANYTHING FOR CHRISTMAS --

01:42.630 --> 01:43.665
ANYTHING --

01:43.670 --> 01:46.696
I WANT YOU
TO SAVE YOUR MONEY.

01:46.700 --> 01:48.338
OH, HEY, HEY, HEY.

01:48.340 --> 01:50.501
OH, IT'S OUR FAVORITE PART!

01:52.010 --> 01:55.309
* I'M MR. GREEN CHRISTMAS *

01:55.310 --> 01:58.177
* I'M MR. SUN *

01:58.180 --> 02:01.115
Duncan:
* I'M MR. HEAT BLISTER *

02:01.120 --> 02:03.588
* I'M MR. HUNDRED-AND-ONE *

02:03.590 --> 02:06.582
* THEY CALL ME
HEAT MISER, HEY *

02:06.590 --> 02:09.718
* WHATEVER I TOUCH
STARTS TO MELT *

02:09.730 --> 02:12.528
YOU START SINGING,
YOU STOP DRINKING.

02:12.530 --> 02:13.997
OH.

02:14.000 --> 02:16.321
YOU LOOK PRETI'Y COMFORTABLE
WITH THAT THING IN YOUR MOUTH.

02:16.330 --> 02:18.195
SABOR CUBANO.

02:18.200 --> 02:21.067
YOU PEOPLE CAN HAND-ROLL
LIKE NOBODY'S BUSINESS.

02:21.070 --> 02:22.833
[ LAUGHTER ]

02:25.710 --> 02:27.075
500.

02:27.080 --> 02:28.707
CALL.

02:28.710 --> 02:29.779
[ GRUNTS ]

02:29.780 --> 02:32.613
SEAN, ISN'T THAT GHE'I'I'O BREW
BENEATH YOU?

02:32.620 --> 02:33.746
IT'S THE NEW ME.

02:33.750 --> 02:36.639
I AM PROJECTING
A GHETTO AESTHETIC.

02:36.650 --> 02:37.480
WORD.

02:37.490 --> 02:38.980
MAN, WHERE WERE YOU

02:38.990 --> 02:41.515
WHEN I WAS PLAYING THE
METROSEXUAL IN "LONELY SEASON"?

02:41.520 --> 02:43.249
I WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL,
NOT GETTING PAID

02:43.260 --> 02:45.956
A QUARTER OF A MILLION DOLLARS
TO MAKE OUT WITH SELMA BLAIR.

02:45.960 --> 02:48.622
CONNOR, DON'T CRY NOW.

02:48.630 --> 02:50.723
OOH-HOO!

02:50.730 --> 02:52.869
ALL IN.

02:54.640 --> 02:55.629
BOO...

02:55.640 --> 02:57.369
HOO.

02:58.440 --> 03:01.000
OOH'
HOOI

03:01.010 --> 03:02.238
OH.

03:02.250 --> 03:04.502
OH! DAMN!

03:04.510 --> 03:06.512
[ LAUGHS ]
SO, LET'S SEE HERE.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.442
THERE ARE
42 CARDS REMAINING,

03:08.450 --> 03:10.611
AND I CAN WIN
WITH 40 OF THEM.

03:10.620 --> 03:14.386
I CAN WIN WITH AN ACE.
I CAN WIN WITH A JACK.

03:14.390 --> 03:16.449
WILL SHE BE THE 10
AND GIVE ME THE STRAIGHT?

03:16.460 --> 03:19.327
OR WILL I GET THE HIGH KICKER
OUT OF MY JACK?

03:20.460 --> 03:21.950
PINS AND NEEDLES, MAN.

03:21.960 --> 03:23.496
JUST FLIP THE CARD.

03:23.500 --> 03:24.660
OKAY.

03:24.670 --> 03:27.594
* BUT THE RIVER
IS GONNA GETCHA *

03:31.840 --> 03:32.875
BOOM!

03:32.880 --> 03:35.508
[ LAUGHTER ]

03:37.910 --> 03:42.040
I CAN'T BELIEVE HE BEAT YOU
WITH A PAIR OF 25.

03:42.050 --> 03:43.415
I'D LIKE MY 5 GRAND NOW.

03:43.420 --> 03:47.288
SEAN, THE MONEY BOX,
SO I CAN PAY THE POOL BOY.

03:59.030 --> 04:00.497
NO. NO, NO, NO.

04:00.500 --> 04:03.663
YOU GUYS AREN'T PULLING
ANY OF THAT WITH ME.

04:03.670 --> 04:06.309
WEEVIL, I'M NOT
PULLING ANYTHING.

04:06.310 --> 04:07.902
WHERE'S THE MONEY?

04:08.580 --> 04:09.842
GUYS, WHERE'S THE MONEY?

04:09.850 --> 04:11.408
WHERE IS IT?!
GUYS, WHERE'S THE MONEY?!

04:11.410 --> 04:13.469
DID IT FALL OUT?
HOW COULD IT FALL OUT?

04:13.480 --> 04:15.072
MAYBE IT WAS NEVER IN,
HUH?

04:15.080 --> 04:18.447
I ROLLED THE MONEY UP AND PUT IT
IN THE BOX. YOU ALL SAW ME.

04:18.450 --> 04:21.851
WELL, I'M NOT LEAVING HERE
WITHOUT MY MONEY.

04:21.860 --> 04:25.523
NOW, DO I HAVE TO TURN
EACH OF YOU UPSIDE DOWN

04:25.530 --> 04:27.259
AND SHAKE YOU?

04:33.740 --> 04:36.265
DID YOU GUYS
CALL EACH OTHER?

04:40.340 --> 04:41.739
THIS ISN'T OVER.

04:41.740 --> 04:45.449
I'LL BE COLLECTING A GRAND
FROM EACH OF YOU,

04:45.450 --> 04:47.645
ONE WAY OR ANOTHER.

04:49.250 --> 04:52.481
YOU PICKED THE WRONG GUY
TO RIP OFF.

04:54.960 --> 04:56.382
[ SIGHS ]

04:56.390 --> 04:59.928
THIS IS THE WORST GAME
OF STRIP POKER EVER.

04:59.930 --> 05:04.026
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

05:04.030 --> 05:10.139
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

05:10.140 --> 05:12.472
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR *

05:12.480 --> 05:15.233
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

05:15.240 --> 05:18.038
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN *

05:18.050 --> 05:20.075
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

05:20.080 --> 05:25.643
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

05:33.130 --> 05:34.449
CHECK IT OUT.

05:34.460 --> 05:35.927
YOU KNOW THIS IS FOR
A BASEBALL CAMP, RIGHT?

05:35.930 --> 05:37.921
IT'S NOT, LIKE,
A HOT-GUY CATALOG.

05:37.930 --> 05:39.795
DO THEY HAVE
A HOT-GUY CATALOG?

05:39.800 --> 05:41.859
ATI'END A WEEK-LONG
PADRES FANTASY CAMP

05:41.870 --> 05:43.861
AT THEIR
FIRST-CLASS TRAINING SITE.

05:43.870 --> 05:46.532
IT'S THE PERFECT
CHRISTMAS PRESENT FOR MY DAD.

05:46.540 --> 05:48.804
IN A WORLD
WHERE YOU CAN AFFORD 3 GRAND.

05:48.810 --> 05:51.847
OH, I AM SO SICK
OF NOT HAVING MONEY.

05:51.850 --> 05:54.148
I'D BE THE BEST RICH PERSON,
SERIOUSLY.

05:54.150 --> 05:57.847
I'D BE THE PERFECT COMBINATION
OF FRIVOLOUS AND SENSIBLE.

05:57.850 --> 06:00.318
MONEY IS SO WASTED
ON THE WEALTHY.

06:00.320 --> 06:02.288
I WANT MY LAPTOP NOW!

06:02.290 --> 06:05.282
HOW DOES IT FEEL TO WANT?

06:05.290 --> 06:06.757
I AM NOT SCREWING AROUND.

06:06.760 --> 06:09.092
LOOK,
I DIDN'T TAKE YOUR MONEY!

06:09.100 --> 06:10.567
SOMEONE DID.

06:10.570 --> 06:12.492
WELL, IT WASN'T ME!

06:12.500 --> 06:14.388
LET HIM GO.

06:22.450 --> 06:23.849
SOMEONE STOLE YOUR LAPTOP?

06:23.850 --> 06:26.774
THERE WAS THIS POKER GAME
AT LOGAN'S LAST NIGHT.

06:26.780 --> 06:29.886
WEEVIL WON 5 GRAND,
AND SOMEONE STOLE THE MONEY.

06:29.890 --> 06:31.687
THIS IS HIS WAY
OF COLLECTING.

06:31.690 --> 06:34.409
YOU LIE DOWN WITH DOGS,
YOU'RE GONNA GET FLEAS.

06:34.420 --> 06:35.956
I DIDN'T INVITE HIM.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.985
I WASN'T TALKING
ABOUT WEEVIL.

06:37.990 --> 06:41.255
HEY, THIS KIND OF
CONCERNS YOU.

06:41.260 --> 06:42.591
I DON'T SEE HOW.

06:42.600 --> 06:44.124
I KEEP A JOURNAL
ON MY LAPTOP

06:44.130 --> 06:46.894
FOR THE PAST --
I DON'T KNOW -- THREE YEARS.

06:46.900 --> 06:49.835
THERE WAS A TIME
WHEN YOU WERE KIND OF A FEATURE.

06:49.840 --> 06:52.673
A FEATURE WITH
A CLEVERLY DISGUISED PSEUDONYM?

06:52.680 --> 06:55.638
LET'S JUST SAY
I WAS PROLIFIC.

06:55.640 --> 06:57.744
Veronica:
THERE ARE A MILLION THINGS

06:57.750 --> 06:59.741
DUNCAN COULD HAVE WRITTEN
ABOUT ME

06:59.750 --> 07:02.446
THAT I'D SOONER IMPALE MYSELF
ON A RUSTY SPIKE

07:02.450 --> 07:03.883
THAN HAVE SOMEONE ELSE READ.

07:03.890 --> 07:06.450
I MUST GET THAT COMPUTER BACK.

07:08.360 --> 07:09.349
UNH.

07:09.360 --> 07:10.827
OH.

07:11.690 --> 07:13.248
HEY.

07:13.260 --> 07:14.625
[ CHUCKLES ] SEE?

07:14.630 --> 07:16.689
THERE YOU GO
WITH THAT HEAD-TILT THING.

07:16.700 --> 07:18.861
YOU KNOW, YOU THINK
YOU'RE ALL BADASS,

07:18.870 --> 07:22.192
BUT WHENEVER YOU NEED SOMETHING,
IT'S ALL, "HEY."

07:23.040 --> 07:25.964
JUST BE GLAD I DON'T
FLIP MY HAIR. I'D OWN YOU.

07:25.970 --> 07:27.835
SO, WHAT CAN I DO
FOR YOU?

07:27.840 --> 07:30.638
YOU CAN NOT GET BUSTED
STEALING O9ers' STUFF

07:30.650 --> 07:33.210
AND LET ME HANDLE
THIS POKER THING.

07:33.220 --> 07:34.312
[ LAUGHS ]

07:34.320 --> 07:35.810
SERIOUSLY, WHY RISK IT?

07:35.820 --> 07:38.914
GIVE DUNCAN BACK HIS COMPUTER.
LET ME HANDLE THIS.

07:38.920 --> 07:41.184
COULD YOU PLEASE,
VERONICA, PROTECT ME

07:41.190 --> 07:44.523
FROM THE BIG, BAD,
SWEATER-VEST-WEARING RICH BOYS?

07:44.530 --> 07:46.418
I'M JUST TRYING TO HELP.

07:46.430 --> 07:48.193
IN WHAT ALTERNATE UNIVERSE

07:48.200 --> 07:52.193
DOES IT LOOK LIKE
I NEED YOUR HELP, HUH?

07:57.970 --> 08:01.633
SOME OF THOSE GUYS
WILL STOP LOSING THEIR STUFF.

08:03.550 --> 08:05.848
WHY WERE YOU EVEN THERE?

08:06.950 --> 08:12.343
I HEAR ABOUT A $5,000 CARD GAME
PLAYED BY IDIOTS.

08:12.350 --> 08:14.113
I'M INTERESTED.

08:15.860 --> 08:17.282
PFFFT!

08:17.290 --> 08:19.895
IF YOU'RE ASKING ME TO THE PROM
AGAIN, THE ANSWER IS STILL NO.

08:19.900 --> 08:22.323
I HEARD YOU GOT
A CARD GAME GOING ON.

08:22.330 --> 08:23.558
I'D LIKE IN ON IT.

08:23.570 --> 08:25.424
YEAH, I'M SURE YOU WOULD,
BUT I CAN'T.

08:25.430 --> 08:26.738
$1,000 BUY-IN, RIGHT?

08:26.740 --> 08:28.958
I GOT THE MONEY,
SO WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

08:28.970 --> 08:31.131
MY ONLY CONCERN
IS PROPERTY VALUES GOING DOWN

08:31.140 --> 08:32.903
IF ANYONE SEES YOU
IN MY HOUSE

08:32.910 --> 08:34.798
WITHOUT A LEAF BLOWER
OR A SKIMMER.

08:34.810 --> 08:36.232
YOU'RE CONCERNED?

08:36.240 --> 08:39.243
I'M THE ONE WHO'S GOT TO GO
UP INTO THE HILLS

08:39.250 --> 08:40.615
ALL BY MYSELF.

08:40.620 --> 08:42.815
WHAT IF I RUN INTO
A PACK OF YOU WHITE BOYS

08:42.820 --> 08:44.742
ON SOME CLEAN,
WELL-LIT STREET?

08:44.750 --> 08:47.583
I COULD BE BORED
TO DEATH.

08:47.590 --> 08:48.909
FINE.

08:48.920 --> 08:53.220
IT'S $1,000
IN 10 CRISP $100 BILLS.

08:54.800 --> 08:56.722
WE DON'T TAKE FOOD STAMPS.

08:56.730 --> 08:59.290
OUCH! YOU GOT ME!

09:01.870 --> 09:03.963
HE THOUGHT I WAS
JUST SOME DUMB MEXICAN

09:03.970 --> 09:05.301
HE COULD TAKE
FOR HIS CASH.

09:05.310 --> 09:09.098
WHO DO YOU THINK DID IT?
DID LOGAN DO IT?

09:10.550 --> 09:11.972
WELL, I KNOW FOR A FACT

09:11.980 --> 09:13.845
THAT NOBODY LEFI' THE HOUSE
WITH THE MONEY.

09:13.850 --> 09:15.738
HE COULD HAVE HIDDEN IT
ANYWHERE,

09:15.750 --> 09:17.581
AND HE HAD AN OPPORTUNITY.

09:20.290 --> 09:21.917
SEAN WON AGAIN?

09:21.920 --> 09:24.150
YOU MISS A LOT WHEN YOU GO TO
THE BATHROOM EVERY FIVE SECONDS.

09:24.160 --> 09:26.958
TIP MONEY FOR THE GUY
WHO WASHES MY JAG.

09:26.960 --> 09:28.951
YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE
A LICENSE.

09:28.960 --> 09:32.020
DUDE, WHY DOES HE NEED A LICENSE
WHEN HE HAS A CHAUFFEUR?

09:32.030 --> 09:35.568
CAN IT BE CONSIDERED
AN EMBARRASSMENT OF RICHES

09:35.570 --> 09:37.231
IF I'M NOT EMBARRASSED?

09:37.240 --> 09:38.264
THOUGHTS?

09:40.080 --> 09:43.277
HOT CHICK, POOLSIDE,
BIKINI.

09:47.980 --> 09:50.915
DUDE, IS THAT YOUR MOM?

09:50.920 --> 09:52.808
AND HERE'S TO YOU,
MRS. ECHOLLS.

09:52.820 --> 09:54.981
Logan: ALL OF YOU
ARE GONNA ROT IN HELL.

09:54.990 --> 09:57.185
I'LL GO TO CHURCH EVERY DAY
IF THIS A NIGHTLY SKINNY-DIP.

09:57.190 --> 09:59.658
PLEASE JUMP OFF
THE DIVING BOARD.

09:59.660 --> 10:01.799
OH, GOD,
I LOVE YOUR MOTHER.

10:01.800 --> 10:03.620
[ LAUGHTER ]

10:10.170 --> 10:11.933
DUNCAN WAS
AT THE WINDOW?

10:11.940 --> 10:13.532
EVERYBODY BUT LOGAN WAS.

10:13.540 --> 10:14.802
YOU'RE SURE?

10:14.810 --> 10:16.038
I WASN'T TAKING NOTES,
BUT, YEAH.

10:16.040 --> 10:17.905
THE MONEY WAS
IN THAT HOUSE SOMEWHERE.

10:17.910 --> 10:19.343
I WOULD HAVE TORN
THE PLACE APART

10:19.350 --> 10:21.944
IF I DIDN'T THINK
HE'D CALL THE COPS.

10:35.600 --> 10:37.227
I DON'T HAVE
AN APPOINTMENT.

10:37.230 --> 10:39.494
I WAS HOPING
YOU WERE AVAILABLE.

10:39.500 --> 10:41.161
IAM.

10:41.970 --> 10:44.336
I'LL CLEAR THAT FOR YOU.

10:46.910 --> 10:48.605
HOW ARE YOU, LYNN?

10:48.610 --> 10:51.408
HONESTLY,
I-I'M A LITTLE FREAKED OUT.

10:51.410 --> 10:55.369
MY HUSBAND GETS A LOT
OF DISTURBING LETTERS FROM FANS.

10:55.380 --> 10:59.282
HE'S A VERY HANDSOME MAN,
AND PEOPLE GET OBSESSED.

10:59.290 --> 11:02.179
EVERYBODY HAS THEIR CROSS
TO BEAR, HUH?

11:02.190 --> 11:04.249
WELL,
THIS ONE'S DIFFERENT.

11:04.260 --> 11:07.297
I FOUND THIS ON OUR
BREAKFAST TABLE IN OUR HOUSE.

11:07.300 --> 11:09.962
"CHEATER, CHEATER,
PUMPKIN EATER,

11:09.970 --> 11:12.291
HAD A WIFE
AND COULDN'T KEEP HER."

11:12.300 --> 11:14.689
CAN YOU FIND HER
AND KEEP HER AWAY FROM US?

11:14.700 --> 11:16.258
OBVIOUSLY, SHE'S CRAZY.

11:16.270 --> 11:17.407
NOT NECESSARILY A SHE.

11:17.410 --> 11:20.208
DO YOU KEEP
ALL THE THREATENING LETTERS?

11:20.210 --> 11:22.098
I TRY TO --
AARON THROWS THEM OUT,

11:22.110 --> 11:23.975
BUT I THOUGHT
WE MIGHT NEED THEM.

11:23.980 --> 11:26.039
I'D LIKE TO SEE THEM,
IF I MAY,

11:26.050 --> 11:29.178
JUST TO DETERMINE WHETHER
THIS IS THE FIRST LETTER.

11:29.180 --> 11:31.580
CAN I COME BY
THIS AFTERNOON?

11:31.590 --> 11:33.888
PERFECT.

11:37.230 --> 11:41.553
I KNOW THIS GOES WITHOUT SAYING,
BUT DISCRETION'S PARAMOUNT.

11:41.560 --> 11:42.788
OF COURSE.

11:42.800 --> 11:44.427
IT'S BEEN
A LONG TIME, KEITH.

11:44.430 --> 11:48.036
OUR KIDS DON'T SEEM TO HANG OUT
TOGETHER MUCH ANYMORE.

11:48.040 --> 11:50.235
LOGAN'S HAD A TOUGH TIME
WITH LILLY'S DEATH.

11:50.240 --> 11:53.698
UNDERSTANDABLY.
SO HAS VERONICA.

11:59.150 --> 12:00.276
GOOD NEWS.

12:00.280 --> 12:02.942
I MIGHT BE ABLE
TO GET YOUR LAPTOP BACK.

12:02.950 --> 12:06.147
SO, WHAT IS THIS,
LIKE, A CASE?

12:06.150 --> 12:08.084
LIKE THE CASE OF THE GUY
WHO'S TOO LAZY

12:08.090 --> 12:10.684
TO HANDWRITE HIS JOURNAL,
LIKE EVERY NORMAL PERSON.

12:10.690 --> 12:12.089
[ LAUGHS ]

12:12.090 --> 12:15.753
SO, ANY DETAILS
YOU CAN GIVE ME?

12:18.030 --> 12:19.566
YOU'RE SERIOUS.

12:19.570 --> 12:22.835
WERE YOU A LITTLE SURPRISED
THAT WEEVIL WAS EVEN THERE?

12:22.840 --> 12:24.967
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I WAS.

12:24.970 --> 12:27.177
JUST WANT
TO LET YOU KNOW --

12:27.180 --> 12:29.740
I AM, IN FACT,
FEELING LUCKY.

12:29.740 --> 12:32.743
WHAT'S UP, BUDDY?
WHAT'S UP?

12:32.750 --> 12:35.878
HELLO.
YOU'RE NOT CHESTER.

12:36.750 --> 12:38.843
DON'T WORRY, OKAY?

12:38.850 --> 12:40.386
THERE'S NO WAY IN HELL

12:40.390 --> 12:42.824
I'M LETTING WEEVIL
WALK OUT OF HERE WITH OUR MONEY.

12:54.670 --> 13:00.108
DO YOU THINK LOGAN INVITED
WEEVIL THERE TO STEAL HIS MONEY?

13:00.110 --> 13:02.806
INVITED HIM THERE
TO STEAL HIS MONEY?

13:02.810 --> 13:04.072
NO.

13:04.080 --> 13:05.274
BUT?

13:08.220 --> 13:09.812
NOTHING.

13:13.220 --> 13:15.211
THAT'S WHAT HE DECIDES
TO STEAL?

13:15.220 --> 13:17.427
WHAT'S HE GONNA DO
WITH A FABERG EGG?

13:17.430 --> 13:21.321
TWO WORDS, MAN --
HUEVOS RANCHEROS.

13:21.330 --> 13:22.524
[ LAUGHTER ]

13:22.530 --> 13:24.862
THIS IS WHAT I GET
FOR TRYING TO BE NICE.

13:29.300 --> 13:32.758
IF YOU GOT SOMETHING TO SAY
TO ME, YOU SAY IT, HUH?

13:32.770 --> 13:34.431
DID YOU TAKE THE MONEY?

13:36.040 --> 13:38.076
DUDE, YOU WERE SO DRUNK,
YOU WOULDN'T KNOW

13:38.080 --> 13:40.173
IF KRISS KRINGLE WALKED IN
AND TOOK THE MONEY.

13:40.180 --> 13:41.716
WHEN DID YOU GET
LIKE THIS?

13:41.720 --> 13:44.211
IT'S LIKE YOU'VE BEEN GOING
TO THE DARK SIDE BIT BY BIT,

13:44.220 --> 13:46.347
SO SLOWLY
THAT I DIDN'T NOTICE

13:46.350 --> 13:49.717
WHEN YOU MORPHED INTO
A FULL-FLEDGED JACKASS.

13:49.720 --> 13:51.722
WHAT, I'M A JACKASS?

13:51.730 --> 13:52.822
YEAH.

13:52.830 --> 13:55.094
AND I'M OVER IT.

13:55.100 --> 13:57.466
WHAT, ARE WE BREAKING UP
NOW, HUH?

13:57.470 --> 14:00.234
YOU WANT
YOUR BEST-FRIEND CHARM BACK?

14:02.470 --> 14:07.305
Lynn: I TRY TO MAKE EACH
CHRISTMAS AS SPECIAL AS I CAN.

14:09.040 --> 14:11.201
CARLITA, BALD PATCH.

14:11.210 --> 14:13.940
WELL, I WENT THROUGH
THE LETTERS YOU GAVE ME,

14:13.950 --> 14:16.145
AND I'M FAIRLY CERTAIN
THAT THE STALKER

14:16.150 --> 14:19.984
WHO LEI-T THE LETTER INSIDE
HAD SENT SIX PREVIOUS LETTERS.

14:19.990 --> 14:21.457
IS IT BAD?

14:21.460 --> 14:23.428
I'M VERY CONCERNED
THAT THIS STALKER

14:23.430 --> 14:25.284
HAS ESCALATED
TO HOME DELIVERY.

14:25.290 --> 14:27.497
I HAVE 200 GUESTS COMING HERE
TOMORROW NIGHT,

14:27.500 --> 14:29.968
AND NOW I HAVE TO DEAL
WITH THIS?

14:29.970 --> 14:31.289
I RECOMMEND
YOU CANCEL THE PARTY.

14:31.300 --> 14:35.031
I'VE HIRED PLENTY
OF SECURITY.

14:35.040 --> 14:37.008
WELL,
WHAT ABOUT THESE PEOPLE?

14:37.010 --> 14:39.137
YOU HAVE 10 PEOPLE
WANDERING FREELY

14:39.140 --> 14:41.028
AROUND YOUR HOUSE
RIGHT NOW.

14:41.040 --> 14:42.268
DO YOU EVEN KNOW THEM?

14:42.280 --> 14:44.646
OF COURSE.
THEY'RE THE HELP.

14:44.650 --> 14:47.039
Aaron: * DECK THE HALLS
WITH BOUGHS OF HOLLY *

14:47.050 --> 14:49.018
* FA LA LA LA LA-- *
HEREYOU GO.

14:49.020 --> 14:50.578
KEITH.

14:50.590 --> 14:54.048
LYNN DIDN'T GET YOU OVER HERE
ABOUT THAT LETTER, DID SHE?

14:54.060 --> 14:56.278
I GET LETTERS LIKE THAT
ALL THE TIME.

14:56.290 --> 15:00.226
I STILL THINK IT'S WISE
TO USE EXTRA CAUTION.

15:00.230 --> 15:02.425
WELL,
I'LL KEEP THAT IN MIND.

15:02.430 --> 15:05.991
LOOK, I'M SORRY
WE BOTHERED YOU ABOUT THIS.

15:06.000 --> 15:07.433
IT'S NOTHING.
TRUST ME.

15:07.440 --> 15:11.501
I MEAN, THAT SORT OF THING
IS PERFECT LY NORMAL.

15:15.010 --> 15:17.547
NORMAL?

15:24.050 --> 15:25.915
I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU DID PUMPKIN CARVING.

15:25.920 --> 15:28.559
YES, I'M AWARE
THAT IT'S CHRISTMAS.

15:28.560 --> 15:32.155
YOU KNOW, I ALREADY HAVE
A GINGERBREAD HOUSE,

15:32.160 --> 15:34.048
BUT THANK YOU.

15:36.430 --> 15:38.591
MAKING A LIST
AND CHECKING IT TWICE.

15:38.600 --> 15:41.068
IS THERE A SIDE JOB
I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?

15:41.070 --> 15:42.867
DO WE NOT LIVE
IN CALIFORNIA?

15:42.870 --> 15:45.998
ISN'T THERE PRODUCE AVAILABLE
365 DAYS A YEAR?

15:46.010 --> 15:48.638
WELL, AT LEAST NOW I KNOW
WHAT I'M GETTING YOU.

15:48.640 --> 15:52.576
HEY, DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE TO RUN
BY THE ECHOLLS' HOUSE FOR ME?

15:52.580 --> 15:55.276
I NEED LYNN TO SIGN
A FEW PAPERS.

15:56.750 --> 15:58.342
SURE.

16:02.020 --> 16:05.524
[GUNFIRE ]

16:05.530 --> 16:06.724
COME ON.

16:06.730 --> 16:09.221
AAH!

16:10.530 --> 16:12.521
COME ON.

16:12.530 --> 16:13.792
DIE.

16:13.800 --> 16:16.963
I LOVE THE SMELL OF TESTOSTERONE
IN THE MORNING.

16:16.970 --> 16:19.302
THIS IS WHY
I SUGGESTED ATTACK DOGS,

16:19.310 --> 16:21.505
BUT, NO, MY MOTHER WANTED
AN ALPACA.

16:21.510 --> 16:25.571
MY FATHER SENT ME
WITH PAPERWORK FOR YOUR MOM.

16:25.580 --> 16:27.775
AND YOU JUST WANTED
TO SAY HI?

16:28.520 --> 16:30.681
IT'S A GOOD THING
I DIDN'T HAVE MY SLAM BOOK OUT.

16:30.690 --> 16:32.783
I WANTED TO ASK YOU
ABOUT THE GAME.

16:32.790 --> 16:35.884
AND I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO ASK YOU SOMETHING.

16:35.890 --> 16:40.224
DID YOUR SUPER SLEUTH KIT
COME WITH A DECODER RING?

16:40.230 --> 16:43.688
DO YOU HAVE A PEN THAT WRITES
WITH INVISIBLE INK?

16:43.700 --> 16:47.136
NEVER MIND. DON'T CARE.
MUSH, MUSH.

16:49.070 --> 16:51.334
HEY, UH, WAIT.

16:51.340 --> 16:52.466
HEY.

16:53.280 --> 16:56.431
HEY, MAYBE YOU SHOULD TALK
TO CONNOR, HMM?

16:58.910 --> 17:00.116
LARKIN?

17:00.120 --> 17:01.348
LIKE CONNOR LARKIN?

17:01.350 --> 17:04.183
LOOK, HE'S A MORTAL.
BELIEVE ME.

17:04.190 --> 17:05.817
THEY JUST DRAW HIS ABS ON.

17:05.820 --> 17:07.811
IS HE DOING ANOTHER MOVIE
WITH YOUR FATHER?

17:07.820 --> 17:10.380
YOU KNOW, I DON'T KNOW
IF IT'S SO MUCH A MOVIE

17:10.390 --> 17:11.982
AS A $50 MILLION
CRAP PILE.

17:11.990 --> 17:14.788
WHY WOULD CONNOR STEAL
THE MONEY? HE'S A ZILLIONAIRE.

17:14.800 --> 17:18.463
WELL, EVERYBODY'S
GOT THEIR ISSUES, RIGHT?

17:18.470 --> 17:19.619
[ SNIFFS ]

17:19.630 --> 17:22.497
PLUS, THE GUY'S
GOT SOMETHING AGAINST ME.

17:23.440 --> 17:26.329
SO, WHAT'S
CATHERINE ZETA-JONES LIKE?

17:26.340 --> 17:28.228
SHE LIKES TO READ
TO STARVING CHILDREN

17:28.240 --> 17:29.673
AND BAKE HOMEMADE SCONES.

17:29.680 --> 17:31.648
THIS ACCORDING
TO "THE INSIDER."

17:31.650 --> 17:33.675
I ONLY MET HER
IN PASSING.

17:33.680 --> 17:36.717
IT'S NOT LIKE YOUR PEOPLE.
THEY DON'T ALL KNOW EACH OTHER.

17:37.850 --> 17:39.943
DUDE,
WHAT'S UP WITH THAT?

17:39.950 --> 17:41.486
WHAT?

17:41.490 --> 17:43.128
THAT'S, LIKE, THE 10th
RACIST THING YOU'VE SAID.

17:43.130 --> 17:44.529
OH, MY GOD.

17:44.530 --> 17:47.852
DOES THE SOAPBOX COME
WITH THE SAG CARD?

17:47.860 --> 17:49.498
[ CHUCKLING ]

17:49.500 --> 17:54.039
OR IS IT BECAUSE ROSIE PEREZ
THOUGHT YOU WERE A GIRL?

17:54.040 --> 17:55.291
WHAT?

17:55.300 --> 17:57.063
WAIT, WAIT.
THIS, I GOTTA HEAR.

17:57.070 --> 17:58.367
WHEN LOGAN WAS, LIKE, 10,

17:58.370 --> 18:00.873
HE WAS MADLY IN LOVE
WITH ROSIE PEREZ.

18:00.880 --> 18:02.700
YOU SO DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

18:02.710 --> 18:05.941
AARON ARRANGED FOR HER
TO COME TO HIS BIRTHDAY PARTY.

18:05.950 --> 18:07.872
IT WAS, LIKE,
THIS BIG MOMENT.

18:07.880 --> 18:09.609
SHE WALKS IN
WITH THIS GII-T,

18:09.620 --> 18:13.078
AND SHE'S LIKE,
"HAPPY BIRTHDAY, LAUREN."

18:13.090 --> 18:16.059
[ LAUGHTER ]

18:16.760 --> 18:19.854
THAT'S FUNNY.
REALLY HYSTERICAL.

18:19.860 --> 18:22.920
DUDE,
SHE GOT YOU A PURSE.

18:22.930 --> 18:23.965
[ LAUGHTER ]

18:24.770 --> 18:27.898
CONNOR, YOU REALLY ARE LIKE
THE SON AARON ECHOLLS NEVER HAD.

18:27.900 --> 18:29.891
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

18:29.900 --> 18:32.004
DO YOU STILL HAVE
THE PURSE?

18:32.010 --> 18:34.729
[ LAUGHTER ]

18:35.540 --> 18:38.805
SO UNLESS HIS PAVLOVIAN RESPONSE
TO A DOWNLOADED RING TONE

18:38.810 --> 18:42.075
IS TO URINATE,
THEN HE WAS UP TO SOMETHING.

18:42.080 --> 18:44.548
OR HIS BLADDER'S
AS SMALL AS HIS BRAIN.

18:44.550 --> 18:47.018
I WOULD BE MORE THAN HAPPY
TO QUESTION HIM.

18:47.020 --> 18:50.228
I'VE A FEELING HE'S NOT
THE EASIEST PERSON TO GET TO --

18:50.230 --> 18:53.085
PROBABLY HAS A TEAM
OF BODYGUARDS TO PROTECT HIM

18:53.090 --> 18:54.489
FROM GIRLS LIKE ME.

18:54.500 --> 18:56.127
I HONESTLY DON'T GET IT.

18:56.130 --> 18:59.122
HEY, MAN.
IT'S LOGAN ECHOLLS.

18:59.130 --> 19:00.495
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:00.500 --> 19:04.368
YEAH, HEY, LISTEN,
CAN YOU GET MY FRIEND...

19:04.370 --> 19:08.807
A DRIVE-ON TODAY
TO SEE CONNOR?

19:08.810 --> 19:11.040
YEAH, VERONICA MARS.

19:11.050 --> 19:13.712
NO, VERONICA.
"V" AS IN "VIRGIN."

19:13.720 --> 19:15.745
YEAH.

19:17.690 --> 19:18.509
THERE YOU GO.

19:18.520 --> 19:19.942
LOOK AT YOU, ALL HELPFUL.

19:19.950 --> 19:23.113
HEY, YOUR PESKINESS
BEING UNLEASHED ON CONNOR

19:23.120 --> 19:24.883
BRINGS ME JOY.

19:24.890 --> 19:29.827
ANNOY, TINY BLOND ONE.
ANNOY LIKE THE WIND.

19:29.830 --> 19:31.866
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

19:36.740 --> 19:38.367
Director: ACTION!

19:39.270 --> 19:41.773
[ GUNFIRE, EXPLOSIONS ]

19:45.510 --> 19:47.478
ALL RIGHT, NOT BAD.
THAT'S A CUT.

19:47.480 --> 19:49.516
LET'S SET IT UP
TO GO AGAIN, PLEASE.

19:49.520 --> 19:52.512
Veronica: I DON'T KNOW IF
CONNOR'S SMILE COST A MILLION,

19:52.520 --> 19:55.011
BUT HIS SIX-PACK ABS
ARE WORTH AT LEAST DOUBLE THAT.

19:55.020 --> 19:56.419
DAMN!

19:57.990 --> 20:00.185
I REPEAT -- DAMN!

20:00.190 --> 20:01.191
TOO SHINY?

20:01.200 --> 20:03.521
UH...NO.

20:03.530 --> 20:05.623
MY HELICOPTER GETS SHOT DOWN
MIDFLIGHT,

20:05.630 --> 20:09.430
SO I'M SUPPOSED TO BE SWEATY,
BUT I DON'T WANT TO BE GROSS.

20:11.040 --> 20:12.632
I THINK YOU'RE GOOD.

20:12.640 --> 20:16.201
SO, UH, LET ME GUESS --
YOU WANT TO BE AN ACTRESS.

20:16.210 --> 20:18.644
NO, NO. I'M JUST
YOUR STANDARD-ISSUE FAN.

20:18.650 --> 20:22.472
LOGAN TOLD ME YOU WERE
AT THE POKER GAME AND --

20:22.480 --> 20:24.016
OH, YEAH.
THAT WAS FUN.

20:24.020 --> 20:26.648
I HEARD IT GOT WEIRD.
SOMEONE STOLE ALL THE MONEY?

20:26.650 --> 20:29.187
YEAH. I FEEL SORRY
FOR THE KID WHO WON, TOO.

20:29.190 --> 20:32.921
HE WAS PRETTY COOL. HE WAS REAL.
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?

20:32.930 --> 20:35.296
ANY IDEA WHO TOOK IT?

20:35.300 --> 20:37.621
COULD HAVE BEEN ANYONE.

20:39.470 --> 20:42.291
AS I UNDERSTAND IT,
NO ONE LEI-T THE ROOM,

20:42.300 --> 20:44.530
AND IT WOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN POSSIBLE

20:44.540 --> 20:47.737
FOR ANYONE TO WALK OUT
WITH CASH ON THEM.

20:47.740 --> 20:48.968
YOU KNOW WHAT?

20:48.980 --> 20:51.107
THERE WAS ONE GUY
WHO LEI-T THE ROOM WITH CASH.

20:51.110 --> 20:52.771
HOW CAN YOU PLAY CARDS

20:52.780 --> 20:54.919
WHEN YOU CAN'T EVEN GET
YOUR WALLET OUT OF YOUR POCKET?

20:54.920 --> 20:56.569
HOW DOES HE KEEP
WINNING HANDS?

20:56.580 --> 20:59.140
AT LEAST
I TAKE OUT MY WALLET,

20:59.150 --> 21:01.311
UNLIKE
SOME CHEAP-ASS PEOPLE.

21:01.320 --> 21:02.617
IF I DIDN'T KNOW BETTER,

21:02.620 --> 21:04.019
I'D THINK
YOU WERE SPEAKING ILL OF ME.

21:04.030 --> 21:06.487
DUDE, YOU GET DROPPED OFF
IN A TOWN CAR,

21:06.490 --> 21:08.629
AND YOU CAN'T EVEN
CHIP IN FOR BEER.

21:08.630 --> 21:11.895
I HAPPEN TO ENJOY
MY GHETTO BREW AFFECT ATION.

21:11.900 --> 21:12.969
QUENCHING.

21:12.970 --> 21:14.631
YOU ENJOY
BEING A TIGHTWAD.

21:14.640 --> 21:17.438
THANKS FOR COMING OUT.
THANK YOU.

21:17.440 --> 21:19.499
WAIT. HOW MUCH
DID YOU TIP HIM?

21:19.510 --> 21:22.001
DUDE, I DON'T KNOW --
A COUPLE BUCKS.

21:22.010 --> 21:25.173
DUDE, THE BILL WAS $50.
THAT'S LIKE 4%.

21:25.180 --> 21:27.273
LOOK WHO'S GOT
BEER BRAINS.

21:27.280 --> 21:28.770
HERE, MAN.

21:30.020 --> 21:31.282
HERE.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.554
THAT'S A KINDER,
GENTLER WEEVIL.

21:33.560 --> 21:37.849
IT'S CHRISTMAS,
EVEN FOR DELIVERY GUYS.

21:37.860 --> 21:40.078
PA-RUM-PUM-PUM.

21:40.900 --> 21:43.960
REALLY, ANYONE COULD HAVE GOTTEN
HIS HANDS ON THE MONEY BOX.

21:43.970 --> 21:47.394
THERE WERE PLENTY OF TIMES --
BATHROOM BREAKS, BEER BREAKS.

21:47.400 --> 21:48.731
LYNN ECHOLLS BREAKS?

21:48.740 --> 21:51.766
OH, YEAH,
YOU HEARD ABOUT THAT ONE, HUH?

21:52.310 --> 21:54.528
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

21:57.010 --> 22:00.639
IT'S MY AGENT.
CAN YOU EXCUSE ME?

22:01.880 --> 22:04.144
[ DIALING ]

22:04.150 --> 22:08.154
WALLACE, ARE YOU STILL
IN THE ATTENDANCE OFFICE?

22:08.160 --> 22:11.186
IT'S A SMALL FAVOR -- TEENY.

22:11.190 --> 22:13.021
SEAN FREEDRICK'S HOME ADDRESS.

22:13.030 --> 22:15.919
I WANT TO SEND HIM
A CHRISTMAS CARD.

22:21.970 --> 22:23.335
HEY.

22:23.340 --> 22:26.707
I WAS HOPING WE COULD HAVE
A QUICK CONVERSATION IN PRIVATE.

22:26.710 --> 22:30.271
BRIAN'S COOL. YOU CAN TALK
FREELY IN FRONT OF HIM.

22:31.150 --> 22:34.677
AARON, WERE YOU WITH ANYONE
LAST HALLOWEEN

22:34.680 --> 22:39.049
THAT MIGHT BE HARBORING
SOME RESENTMENT OR ILL WILL?

22:39.050 --> 22:40.347
NO.

22:40.350 --> 22:41.851
I WAS THINKING
THAT THE, YOU KNOW,

22:41.860 --> 22:45.057
AARON-O-LANTERN
HAD SOME SIGNIFICANCE --

22:45.060 --> 22:47.324
A SPURNED LOVER, PERHAPS.

22:47.330 --> 22:48.991
I'M FAITHFUL TO MY WIFE.

22:49.000 --> 22:51.696
AS A MATTER OF FACT, I WAS
WITH WITH LYNN LAST HALLOWEEN

22:51.700 --> 22:53.691
AT THE CASABLANCAS'
ANNUAL COSTUME PARTY.

22:53.700 --> 22:58.069
I WAS JUST MAKING SURE.
YOU UNDERSTAND.

22:58.070 --> 23:00.300
WELL, I APPRECIATE THAT.

23:00.310 --> 23:03.507
DON'T WANT TO STIR UP
ANY MUCK.

23:03.510 --> 23:06.638
WELL,
THERE'S NO MUCK TO STIR.

23:11.190 --> 23:12.282
MR. FREEDRICK?

23:12.290 --> 23:13.416
GOOD AFTERNOON.

23:13.420 --> 23:14.455
IS SEAN HOME?

23:14.460 --> 23:15.950
HE'S NOT AVAILABLE.

23:15.960 --> 23:19.225
SEAN IS NOT PERMITTED
TO RECEIVE VISITORS AT HOME.

23:19.230 --> 23:20.788
Woman: MR. FREEDRICK.

23:26.630 --> 23:28.336
I SPOKE
WITH SADIE CASABLANCAS,

23:28.340 --> 23:31.503
AND SHE SAID YOU CATERED
HER HALLOWEEN PARTY LAST YEAR.

23:31.510 --> 23:32.704
I CATER IT EVERY YEAR.

23:32.710 --> 23:34.701
ANYTHING SPECIAL
ABOUT THIS PARTY?

23:34.710 --> 23:37.372
I REALLY CAN'T TALK ABOUT
THE EVENTS WE DO.

23:37.380 --> 23:38.904
IT'S IN THE CONTRACT.

23:38.910 --> 23:40.172
IS THAT SO?

23:40.180 --> 23:41.738
YOU SHOULD KNOW I WAS TOLD

23:41.750 --> 23:45.379
YOU HAD THE BAD TASTE
TO FIRE SOMEONE THAT NIGHT.

23:45.390 --> 23:47.449
SHE DID NOT SAY
"BAD TASTE."

23:47.460 --> 23:49.018
LIKE I HAD A CHOICE.

23:49.020 --> 23:51.784
SERVERS WERE RESTRICTED
TO THE FIRST FLOOR, AS ALWAYS,

23:51.790 --> 23:53.792
BUT ONE SERVER
SNUCK OFF UPSTAIRS

23:53.800 --> 23:55.654
TO FIND
AN AVAILABLE BATHROOM.

23:55.660 --> 23:58.493
AARON ECHOLLS INSISTED
THAT THE GIRL BE FIRED.

23:58.500 --> 24:00.161
AARON WANTED HER FIRED

24:00.170 --> 24:03.196
BECAUSE SHE WAS ON THE SECOND
FLOOR OF SOMEBODY ELSE'S HOUSE?

24:03.200 --> 24:06.601
THAT AND SOMEONE ELSE'S WIFE
WAS ON TOP OF HIM.

24:06.610 --> 24:08.931
WAIT -- YOU'RE SAYING
AARON ECHOLLS

24:08.940 --> 24:12.808
WAS WITH ANOTHER WOMAN THE NIGHT
OF THE HALLOWEEN PARTY?

24:12.810 --> 24:17.645
WHILE HIS WIFE
WAS DOWNSTAIRS EATING CANAPS.

24:42.340 --> 24:43.500
GOOD MORNING.

24:43.510 --> 24:44.807
MAYBE IN YOUR WORLD.

24:44.810 --> 24:46.971
IN MINE,
I AM MINUS ONE ROLEX.

24:46.980 --> 24:48.971
THE CRIMINAL ELEMENT
FOUND ITS WAY

24:48.980 --> 24:50.789
INTO MY GYM BAG
YESTERDAY.

24:50.790 --> 24:52.781
WHY CAN'T WE ALL
JUST HAVE NICE THINGS?

24:52.790 --> 24:54.257
WHO BEHAVES THIS WAY?

24:54.260 --> 24:56.455
MAYBE YOU MISSED
THAT EYE-FOR-AN-EYE SECTION

24:56.460 --> 24:57.859
IN YOUR BIBLE.

24:57.860 --> 24:59.782
OKAY, THIS ISN'T RETRIBUTION.
IT'S THIEVERY.

24:59.790 --> 25:01.155
WEEVIL DIDN'T START THIS.

25:01.160 --> 25:04.266
IT'S NOT HIS FAULT
SOMEONE STOLE THE MONEY.

25:04.270 --> 25:06.522
IS THAT SO?

25:06.530 --> 25:07.736
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

25:07.740 --> 25:10.937
I USUALLY GET SIX FIGURES
FOR THIS.

25:11.570 --> 25:12.867
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

25:12.870 --> 25:14.371
I'M THE ONE
WHO GOT HIS MONEY STOLEN.

25:14.380 --> 25:15.870
I'M THINKING...CRABS?

25:15.880 --> 25:18.599
I TOLD YOUR MOTHER
TO CLEAN UP.

25:18.610 --> 25:20.339
GUYS, PLAY NICE.

25:20.350 --> 25:22.614
I'M PLAYING NICE.

25:22.620 --> 25:25.009
BELIEVE ME.

25:25.020 --> 25:27.215
WHY WOULD WEEVIL
STEAL HIS OWN MONEY?

25:27.220 --> 25:30.383
YOU SHOULD REALLY CONSIDER
ANOTHER PROFESSION.

25:30.390 --> 25:31.755
PERHAPS HE STOLE THE MONEY

25:31.760 --> 25:33.899
BEFORE HE KNEW
HE WAS GOING TO WIN.

25:36.630 --> 25:38.325
HE WAS DOWN
TO HIS LAST TWO CHIPS.

25:38.330 --> 25:40.992
I HEARD YOU WEREN'T
DOING SO HOT, EITHER.

25:41.000 --> 25:45.232
YEAH, BUT THE DIFFERENCE IS,
I DON'T NEED THE MONEY.

25:51.950 --> 25:54.168
FOR THE CASABLANCAS'
HALLOWEEN PARTY.

25:54.180 --> 25:56.614
DO YOU MIND GETTING THAT
FOR ME?

25:56.620 --> 25:58.588
THAN KS.

26:01.190 --> 26:05.229
APPARENTLY, YOU WERE CAUGHT
IN FLAGRANTE.

26:07.960 --> 26:10.929
YEAH, MY MEMORY ISN'T WHAT
IT USED TO BE, EITHER.

26:10.930 --> 26:12.989
LISTEN,
IT DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING.

26:13.000 --> 26:15.332
WHAT'S IT GONNA MEAN?

26:15.340 --> 26:16.659
I LOVE MY WIFE.

26:16.670 --> 26:18.831
AARON, MY JOB
IS TO TRACK DOWN

26:18.840 --> 26:21.070
A POTENTIALLY DANGEROUS
STALKER.

26:21.080 --> 26:25.141
YOUR AFFAIR IS --
WELL, THAT'S YOUR AFFAIR.

26:25.150 --> 26:27.846
SO YOU'RE --
YOU'RE NOT GONNA TELL LYNN?

26:27.850 --> 26:29.943
IF LYNN HAD HIRED ME
TO FIND OUT

26:29.950 --> 26:32.487
IF YOU WERE CHEATING ON HER,
I WOULD TELL HER.

26:32.490 --> 26:36.119
SHE HIRED ME TO PROTECT YOU,
AND THAT'S WHAT I'M GONNA DO,

26:36.120 --> 26:38.088
BUT I'M GONNA NEED
YOUR HELP.

26:38.090 --> 26:41.821
HERE'S THE GUEST LIST FROM THE
CASABLANCAS' HALLOWEEN PARTY.

26:41.830 --> 26:45.061
CIRCLE THE NAME
OF WHO YOU SLEPT WITH.

26:55.640 --> 26:57.232
MAYBE I SHOULD CLARIFY --

26:57.240 --> 27:01.119
WHO YOU SLEPT WITH
AT THE HALLOWEEN PARTY.

27:04.590 --> 27:06.217
[ SIGHS ]

27:06.220 --> 27:08.051
[ CHUCKLES ] OH, GOD.

27:08.060 --> 27:13.282
THAT WAS THE NIGHT
THAT I HAD THE HARD CIDER.

27:16.600 --> 27:19.228
[ LAUGHS ]

27:21.140 --> 27:24.007
THAT WOULD BE
MONICA HADWIN?

27:24.010 --> 27:27.207
YEAH.
BUT SHE'S NOT A STALKER.

27:27.210 --> 27:28.768
SHE'S MY AGENT'S WIFE.

27:28.780 --> 27:30.998
I'M SURE SHE'S LOVELY.

27:32.310 --> 27:37.680
MRS. CASABLANCAS GAVE ME
PHOTOS FROM THE PARTY.

27:37.690 --> 27:39.749
IF YOU COULD POINT OUT
MONICA

27:39.750 --> 27:44.824
AND, UH...
SHARON AND DEBORAH.

27:48.630 --> 27:50.655
OH.

27:52.430 --> 27:54.091
THERE THEY ARE.

27:55.400 --> 28:00.167
THESE THREE WOMEN ARE INVITED
TO YOUR CHRISTMAS PARTY.

28:00.170 --> 28:02.877
MAYBE THAT'S NOT
THE BEST IDEA.

28:02.880 --> 28:04.006
[ SCOFFS ]

28:04.010 --> 28:06.478
THEY'RE NOT STALKERS.

28:06.480 --> 28:08.118
THEY'RE JUST...

28:08.120 --> 28:10.076
NEEDY.

28:11.390 --> 28:14.018
TIGHTER. I DIDN'T LOSE 5 POUNDS
FOR MY HEALTH.

28:14.020 --> 28:15.681
Keith:
SO, MRS. HADWIN...

28:15.690 --> 28:16.918
HADWIN'S MY MAIDEN NAME.

28:16.920 --> 28:19.184
I DIDN'T WANT
TO BE MONICA GREENBLATT.

28:19.190 --> 28:21.021
IF THERE'S ANYTHING ELSE
YOU COULD TELL ME,

28:21.030 --> 28:22.657
IT WOULD BE HELPFUL
TO THE ECHOLLS.

28:22.660 --> 28:25.265
WHAT'S TO TELL -- AARON'S
A SEXY, CHARMING MOVIE STAR

28:25.270 --> 28:27.738
WITH AN ASS
LIKE AN 18-YEAR-OLD WRESTLER.

28:27.740 --> 28:29.298
HE'S PSYCHO BAIT.

28:29.300 --> 28:31.461
CAN WE GO A COUPLE INCHES
HIGHER? IT'S NOT A WAKE.

28:31.470 --> 28:34.177
YOU KNOW WHO YOU SHOULD TALK TO,
IS DEBORAH DALY.

28:34.180 --> 28:36.102
SHE'S ALWAYS HOVERING
AROUND AARON,

28:36.110 --> 28:38.146
STICKING HER FAKE BOOBS
AT HIM.

28:38.150 --> 28:39.572
OKAY, LOOK --

28:39.580 --> 28:41.878
MY LIFE DEPENDS ON LOOKING
AS HOT AS POSSIBLE IN THIS.

28:41.880 --> 28:44.019
YOU'RE GONNA NEED
TO RALLY.

28:44.020 --> 28:46.341
[ SIGHS ]
ALWAYS WITH AN AUDIENCE.

28:46.350 --> 28:49.251
HE'S THE ECHOLLS'
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

28:49.260 --> 28:50.488
AARON HAS A STALKER.

28:50.490 --> 28:51.957
OH.

28:51.960 --> 28:54.121
I'M PROVIDING HIM
WITH THE LOWDOWN ON THE LADIES

28:54.130 --> 28:55.825
THAT AIM HIGHER
THAN TENNIS PRO.

28:55.830 --> 28:58.128
YOU'D THINK AT LEAST ONE PART OF
MY DAY WOULDN'T INVOLVE AARON.

28:58.130 --> 29:00.462
BEFORE AARON,
HIS BIGGEST CLIENT

29:00.470 --> 29:03.667
WAS A DAY PLAYER
ON "BOY MEETS WORLD."

29:03.670 --> 29:05.228
AND BEFORE ME,

29:05.240 --> 29:08.869
YOU SAT IN YOUR UNDERWEAR
IN A FISH TANK AT THE STANDARD.

29:12.380 --> 29:14.371
Veronica: BREATHE, VERONICA.
SO WHAT?

29:14.380 --> 29:16.871
DUNCAN'S SECRET DIARY
IS UNACCOUNTED FOR.

29:16.880 --> 29:18.916
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THE INTIMATE DETAILS

29:18.920 --> 29:20.956
OF OUR STRANGE
AND STEAMY RELATIONSHIP

29:20.960 --> 29:23.110
WILL BECOME PUBLIC DOMAIN
AT NEPTUNE HIGH.

29:23.120 --> 29:25.657
THINGS DON'T ALWAYS TURN OUT
FOR THE WORST.

29:25.660 --> 29:27.025
AI-TER ALL, IT'S CHRISTMAS.

29:27.030 --> 29:28.952
DESPITE WHAT EVERYONE ELSE
MIGHT THINK,

29:28.960 --> 29:30.518
SANTA KNOWS I'VE BEEN
A GOOD GIRL.

29:30.530 --> 29:34.068
YOU'RE GONNA HURT YOURSELF
THINKING THAT HARD.

29:34.070 --> 29:36.265
THEY SAY IF YOU'RE CAUGHT
IN A STARE,

29:36.270 --> 29:37.965
IT MEANS
YOUR MIND NEEDS A BREAK.

29:37.970 --> 29:40.234
LIKE THAT MIND
EVER TAKES A BREAK.

29:40.240 --> 29:42.731
SO, HOW'S
THE POKER CASE COMING?

29:42.740 --> 29:44.241
IT'S A CHRISTMAS MIRACLE.

29:44.250 --> 29:47.139
I THINK I FINALLY FOUND A WAY
TO SEND MY DAD TO CAMP.

29:51.990 --> 29:55.653
WILL YOU GUYS KISS
AND MAKE UP ALREADY?

29:55.660 --> 29:56.888
[ SMOOCHES ]

29:56.890 --> 29:58.357
SO, GOOD NEWS, BAD NEWS.

29:58.360 --> 30:01.557
THE GOOD NEWS IS,
I KNOW WHO STOLE THE MONEY.

30:01.560 --> 30:05.860
THE BAD NEWS IS,
I KNOW WHO STOLE THE MONEY.

30:05.870 --> 30:07.428
HERE'S MY BRILLIANT IDEA.

30:07.430 --> 30:10.900
FILLED WITH HOLIDAY SPIRIT,
LOGAN WILL HOST ANOTHER GAME.

30:10.910 --> 30:12.559
WILL I?
I'M THINKING TONIGHT.

30:12.570 --> 30:15.630
NO, MY MOTHER'S
CHRISTMAS PARTY IS TONIGHT.

30:15.640 --> 30:17.130
HMM.
SO NO B.Y.O.B.

30:17.140 --> 30:19.449
HERE'S HOW IT'LL GO DOWN --
I'LL TELL YOU WHO DID IT,

30:19.450 --> 30:22.078
AND YOU'LL BUY ME
INTO THE GAME.

30:22.080 --> 30:24.548
I'LL JUST TAKE THE PLACE
OF WHOEVER STOLE THE MONEY --

30:24.550 --> 30:27.280
UNLESS YOU THINK YOU MIGHT
STILL WANT HIM AROUND.

30:27.290 --> 30:29.087
YOU KNOW,
EVEN IF YOU KEEP TALKING,

30:29.090 --> 30:30.580
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

30:30.590 --> 30:34.799
OH. I THOUGHT YOU GUYS
MIGHT ALL WANT YOUR STUFF BACK.

30:34.800 --> 30:36.028
YEAH...

30:36.030 --> 30:37.918
IF I GET MY 5 GRAND,

30:37.930 --> 30:40.933
SOME ITEMS
COULD MAGICALLY REAPPEAR.

30:40.940 --> 30:42.567
AND IF YOU THINK
ABOUT IT,

30:42.570 --> 30:45.437
ANYONE WHO DOESN'T SEE THIS
AS A GREAT OFFER

30:45.440 --> 30:46.737
IS OBVIOUSLY THE THIEF.

30:46.740 --> 30:48.037
KIND OF A NO-BRAINER.

30:48.040 --> 30:50.429
DO YOU EVEN KNOW
HOW TO PLAY POKER?

30:50.440 --> 30:52.476
NO.

30:52.480 --> 30:56.348
BUT IT MUST BE REALLY HARD
IF ALL YOU GUYS PLAY.

31:05.830 --> 31:06.854
* JOY TO THE WORLD *

31:06.860 --> 31:09.294
* THE LORD IS COME *

31:09.300 --> 31:13.669
* LET EARTH RECEIVE HER KING *

31:13.670 --> 31:18.437
* LET EVERY HEART
PREPARE HIM ROOM *

31:18.440 --> 31:20.761
* AND HEAVEN AND NATURE SING *

31:20.770 --> 31:23.079
* AND HEAVEN AND NATURE SING *

31:23.080 --> 31:24.968
* AND HEAVEN... *

31:27.780 --> 31:29.247
HO HO...

31:29.250 --> 31:30.148
HO.

31:30.150 --> 31:32.380
[ LAUGHS MOCKINGLY ]

31:32.390 --> 31:33.982
ALLOW ME.

31:35.120 --> 31:37.509
YOU WANT A SODY POP
OR SOMETHING?

31:37.520 --> 31:38.726
YOU KNOW...

31:38.730 --> 31:41.699
I THINK I WANT SOMETHING
WITH A LITTLE MORE KICK.

31:41.700 --> 31:43.349
HEY, NO --

31:44.100 --> 31:46.466
DAMN, GIRL.

31:48.770 --> 31:50.237
MMM.

31:50.240 --> 31:54.438
ICED TEA?
HOW VERY MUSICAL THEATER OF YOU.

31:54.440 --> 31:55.839
[ LAUGHTER ]

31:55.840 --> 31:57.603
DUNCAN CAN'T REMEMBER
THE ALPHABET WHEN HE DRINKS,

31:57.610 --> 32:01.216
LET ALONE FIGURE OUT
20% OF THE PIZZA BILL.

32:01.220 --> 32:04.348
NO, HE DIDN'T PLAY DRUNK
TO STEAL YOUR MONEY.

32:04.350 --> 32:06.318
HE PLAYED DRUNK
TO WIN YOUR MONEY --

32:06.320 --> 32:07.617
TO NO AVAIL, IT SEEMS.

32:07.620 --> 32:10.589
OH, AND CONNOR
ISN'T A DRUG ADDICT.

32:11.290 --> 32:14.919
I KNOW --
THE CONSTANT BATHROOM VISITS.

32:14.930 --> 32:16.989
HE WASN'T GOING FOR A FIX.

32:17.000 --> 32:19.127
HE WAS GOING
BECAUSE OF THE SUN TEA.

32:19.130 --> 32:21.098
IT'S THAT DIURETIC
WRESTLERS DOWN

32:21.100 --> 32:22.499
WHEN THEY NEED TO MAKE WEIGHT

32:22.500 --> 32:26.061
OR THAT ACTORS USE
BEFORE THEY'RE HALF-NAKED

32:26.070 --> 32:28.004
ON THE COVER OF VANITY FAIR.

32:28.480 --> 32:31.938
AND THEN
THERE'S BACHELOR NUMBER THREE,

32:31.950 --> 32:37.240
AND HE'S GOT IT ALL --
MOTIVE, ACCESS...

32:37.250 --> 32:38.808
LOOKS LIKE AN EVILDOER...

32:38.820 --> 32:42.278
[ SNIFFS ]
SMELLS LIKE AN EVILDOER...

32:42.290 --> 32:45.680
BUT, SURPRISINGLY,
NOT SO MUCH.

32:45.690 --> 32:47.248
WEEVIL CLEARED HIM.

32:47.260 --> 32:48.750
HE TOLD ME
HE SEARCHED THE ROOM,

32:48.760 --> 32:51.024
BUT DIDN'T GO THROUGH IT
AS MUCH AS HE WANTED.

32:51.030 --> 32:54.397
WHEN I SAW IT, IT LOOKED LIKE
IT HAD BEEN RAIDED BY THE FBI.

32:54.400 --> 32:56.095
IF LOGAN TOOK THE MONEY
AND HID IT,

32:56.100 --> 32:59.968
HE WOULDN'T HAVE HAD TO TEAR
THE ROOM APART LOOKING FOR IT.

33:01.880 --> 33:03.302
SO TWO LEI-T --

33:03.310 --> 33:05.198
THE BOY FROM THE WRONG SIDE
OF THE TRACKS,

33:05.210 --> 33:08.873
AND THE BOY WHO LIVES
IN THE MOST EXPENSIVE HOUSE

33:08.880 --> 33:10.541
IN THE 09er ZIP.

33:10.550 --> 33:15.180
SO...DO YOU WANT TO HEAR
HOW SEAN DID IT?

33:15.190 --> 33:18.227
OH, HE'S
A CRAFTY LITTLE BUGGER.

33:18.230 --> 33:20.323
SEAN DIDN'T BRING
THE BIGMOUTH JOES

33:20.330 --> 33:21.922
BECAUSE HE'S CHEAP.

33:21.930 --> 33:25.263
HE KNEW HE COULDN'T LEAVE
WITH THE MONEY, SO HE DIDN'T.

33:25.270 --> 33:27.989
WHAT HAPPENS TO GARBAGE
IN THE 09er ZIP?

33:28.300 --> 33:31.360
HE JUST WAITED FOR THE RECYCLING
TO GO OUT THE NEXT DAY

33:31.370 --> 33:34.339
AND DID
A LITTLE GARBAGE PICKING.

33:34.340 --> 33:35.705
SEAN?

33:35.710 --> 33:38.873
THE GUY HAS A CHAUFFEUR
DRIVE HIM TO SCHOOL EVERY DAY.

33:38.880 --> 33:40.472
WHY WOULD HE NEED
TO STEAL?

33:40.480 --> 33:41.811
FUNNY STORY.

33:41.820 --> 33:45.039
WHEN I WENT TO SEAN'S,
I COULDN'T HELP BUT WONDER

33:45.050 --> 33:48.508
WHAT WAS HIS DAD DOING AT HOME
3:00 IN THE AFTERNOON

33:48.520 --> 33:51.250
DRESSED IN A SUIT
INSTEAD OF BEING AT WORK?

33:51.260 --> 33:53.148
Woman: MR. FREEDRICK.

33:53.160 --> 33:55.390
UNLESS HE WAS AT WORK.

33:55.400 --> 33:57.618
I HAVE TO SAY,
I WAS A BIT MIFFED.

33:57.630 --> 34:01.339
I WAS THIS CLOSE TO BEING ABLE
TO SAY THE BUTLER DID IT.

34:01.340 --> 34:03.490
BUT NO --
IT WAS THE BUTLER'S SON.

34:03.500 --> 34:05.764
THAT DOESN'T PROVE
ANYTHING.

34:05.770 --> 34:09.035
THAT PROVES THAT YOU'RE A LIAR,
AND THE BACKGROUND CHECK I RAN

34:09.040 --> 34:12.271
PROVES THAT YOU'VE GOT
A BIT OF A SHOPLIFTING PROBLEM.

34:12.280 --> 34:14.271
YOU ARE REALLY BAD AT IT.

34:20.150 --> 34:21.549
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

34:21.560 --> 34:23.812
I CAN TOTALLY PAY YOU.
I HAVE THE MONEY.

34:25.630 --> 34:27.825
ALL RIGHT.

34:27.830 --> 34:29.149
WHY DON'T WE TAKE A WALK

34:29.160 --> 34:31.390
SO WE CAN DISCUSS
A FEW THINGS, HUH?

34:31.400 --> 34:32.890
BUT, YOU SEE,
I CAN PAY YOU.

34:32.900 --> 34:36.495
THERE'S REALLY NO NEED
FOR PHYSICAL VIOLENCE.

34:36.500 --> 34:38.434
UH-HUH.

34:38.440 --> 34:40.567
MIND IF I DEAL FIRST?

34:54.990 --> 34:57.982
IT'S THIS GREAT WINERY
JUST OUTSIDE OF OJAI.

34:57.990 --> 35:01.926
IT'S 90 MILES, BUT YOU FEEL LIKE
YOU'RE A WORLD AWAY.

35:01.930 --> 35:03.989
Lynn:
OH, IT SOUNDS PERFECT.

35:04.000 --> 35:07.868
GREAT. SO, NEXT FALL,
WE'LL ALL GO FOR THE CRUSH.

35:07.870 --> 35:10.259
OH, I'M SO EXCITED!

35:25.890 --> 35:29.280
[ "JINGLE BELLS" PLAYS ]

35:37.630 --> 35:40.793
MAKE SURE YOU STAY RIGHT HERE
FOR 9:00.

35:40.800 --> 35:45.908
I HAVE A BIG HOLIDAY SURPRISE
FOR EVERYONE.

35:51.780 --> 35:53.805
ELITE CATERING.
THIS IS MARTHA.

35:53.810 --> 35:57.177
THE GIRL YOU FIRED
FROM THE CASABLANCAS' PARTY --

35:57.180 --> 35:58.386
WHAT WAS HER POSITION?

35:58.390 --> 35:59.618
SHE WAS A LE TRANCHER.

35:59.620 --> 36:01.918
WHAT DOES
A LE TRANCHER DO?

36:01.920 --> 36:03.581
THEY'RE CARVERS, SIR.

36:03.590 --> 36:04.659
CARVING?

36:04.660 --> 36:07.424
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT SHE LOOKS LIKE?

36:09.660 --> 36:10.922
[ LAUGHS ]

36:11.970 --> 36:13.323
OH!

36:14.470 --> 36:16.938
A LITTLE IMPRESSED,
AREN'T YOU?

36:16.940 --> 36:19.738
YOU MUST BE REALLY UNLUCKY
IN LOVE.

36:19.740 --> 36:21.207
HA!

36:21.210 --> 36:23.030
OKAY, I SAY WE TAKE
A LITTLE BREAK,

36:23.040 --> 36:26.248
LET THE COSMOS REALIGN,
'CAUSE OBVIOUSLY SOMETHING'S UP.

36:26.250 --> 36:28.343
I CAN USE
SOMETHING TO EAT.

36:33.820 --> 36:38.154
SERIOUSLY,
DON'T I JUST BLEND RIGHT IN?

36:38.160 --> 36:39.184
COME ON.

36:39.190 --> 36:40.726
WHERE'S WEEVIL?

36:40.730 --> 36:42.948
I THINK
WE BOTH STAND OUT A BIT.

36:42.960 --> 36:46.669
YEAH, RIGHT. YOU ARE A NATURAL
AT THIS. LOOK AT YOU.

36:48.470 --> 36:51.303
[ Chuckling ]
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

36:51.310 --> 36:53.904
WILL YOU HOLD THIS
FOR A SEC?

37:01.010 --> 37:02.910
YOU'RE KILLING ME.

37:09.220 --> 37:12.519
SO, I, UH...
YOU KNOW.

37:12.530 --> 37:14.293
YEAH.

37:14.300 --> 37:16.291
I'M SORRY ABOUT
THE WHOLE --

37:16.300 --> 37:18.723
I'VE DONE
PLENTY OF OTHER THINGS.

37:20.400 --> 37:22.595
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

37:25.510 --> 37:27.398
SO WE'RE COOL?

37:29.210 --> 37:30.871
YEAH.

37:33.210 --> 37:34.347
BARTEN DER?

37:34.350 --> 37:36.614
LOOK,
I'M NOT ON THE LIST.

37:36.620 --> 37:40.784
IF YOU COULD JUST TELL AARON
THAT KEITH MARS IS HERE.

37:40.790 --> 37:44.988
WILL YOU LISTEN TO ME?
THIS IS AN EMERGENCY.

37:51.700 --> 37:54.533
I'VE GOT A QUESTION
FOR YOU.

37:54.540 --> 37:56.030
HELLO, VERONICA.

37:56.040 --> 37:58.031
DOES YOUR HEAD OF SECURITY
MAKE IT A HABIT

37:58.040 --> 38:00.133
OF TAKING PHOTOGRAPHS
OF HIGH-SCHOOL STUDENTS

38:00.140 --> 38:03.974
AND DRAWING BULL'S-EYES OVER
THEIR FACES, OR AM I SPECIAL?

38:05.710 --> 38:08.201
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
THE LIST DOESN'T LIE.

38:08.210 --> 38:10.371
[ WOMAN CHUCKLES ]

38:10.380 --> 38:12.280
CLARENCE WIEDMAN
TOOK PICTURES OF ME --

38:12.290 --> 38:13.848
SURVEILLANCE PICTURES.

38:13.850 --> 38:16.557
HE DREW A TARGET OVER MY FACE
AND SENT THEM TO MY MOTHER.

38:16.560 --> 38:18.551
YOU'RE NOT MAKING
ANY SENSE.

38:18.560 --> 38:20.357
WHY DID YOU WANT MY MOTHER
OUT OF TOWN?

38:20.360 --> 38:23.454
I DIDN'T.
WHY DIDN'T SHE TELL ME
OR MY FATHER ABOUT THE PICTURES

38:23.460 --> 38:25.394
INSTEAD OF HIDING THEM
IN A SAFE-DEPOSIT BOX?

38:25.400 --> 38:27.061
I DON'T KNOW!

38:30.600 --> 38:34.707
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

38:50.620 --> 38:53.919
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

38:56.400 --> 38:57.856
WHAT DID YOU DO?

38:57.860 --> 38:59.828
WHAT?
WHAT DID YOU DO?

38:59.830 --> 39:02.298
JAKE, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

39:02.300 --> 39:04.439
DON'T LIE TO ME, CELESTE!

39:04.440 --> 39:06.203
WHAT DID YOU DO?!

39:06.210 --> 39:07.529
JAKE, STOP IT.

39:07.540 --> 39:09.030
GET YOUR COAT.
WE'RE LEAVING.

39:09.040 --> 39:11.941
WELL, I THINK IT'S TIME
FOR US TO GET A DRINK.

39:18.590 --> 39:21.013
[ RINGING ]

39:21.990 --> 39:28.350
EVERYONE, IF YOU COULD
JUST FOLLOW THE SANTAS OUTSIDE,

39:28.360 --> 39:32.262
I HAVE A SPECIAL SURPRISE
FOR YOU.

39:32.270 --> 39:35.091
[ BELLS RINGING ]

39:46.480 --> 39:49.210
BRR.
I'M GONNA GO GRAB MY JACKET.

39:49.220 --> 39:50.778
OKAY.

39:54.720 --> 39:57.689
COME ON, YOU TWO.
YOU'LL MISS THE SURPRISE.

39:57.690 --> 39:59.829
AND WE KNOW HOW MUCH
SHE LOVES A SURPRISE.

39:59.830 --> 40:01.559
YOU DON'T EVEN CARE,
DO YOU?

40:01.560 --> 40:02.857
I'M SORRY?

40:02.860 --> 40:05.169
YOU SLEEP WITH ME.
YOU SAY YOU LOVE ME.

40:05.170 --> 40:09.288
LYNN, I-I-I DON'T KNOW
WHO THIS PERSON IS. I SWEAR.

40:09.300 --> 40:10.562
I DON'T KNOW YOU.

40:11.040 --> 40:12.029
AAAH!

40:12.040 --> 40:13.860
* HERE WE COME A-WASSAILING *

40:13.870 --> 40:15.872
* AMONG THE LEAVES SO GREEN *

40:15.880 --> 40:22.069
* HERE WE COME A-WANDERING,
SO FAIR TO BE SEEN *

40:22.080 --> 40:26.414
* LOVE AND JOY COME TO YOU
AND TO YOU YOUR WASSAIL, TOO *

40:26.420 --> 40:32.052
* AND GOD BLESS YOU
AND SEND YOU A HAPPY NEW YEAR *

40:32.060 --> 40:39.193
* AND GOD SEND YOU
A HAPPY NEW YEAR *

40:40.970 --> 40:43.063
Veronica:
WHAT WAS I THINKING?

40:43.070 --> 40:46.528
CHRISTMAS IN NEPTUNE IS, WAS,
AND ALWAYS WILL BE

40:46.540 --> 40:47.859
ABOUT THE TRAPPINGS --

40:47.870 --> 40:49.974
THE LIGHTS AND THE TINSEL
THEY USE

40:49.980 --> 40:52.778
TO COVER UP THE SORDIDNESS,
THE CORRUPTION.

40:52.780 --> 40:56.648
NO, VERONICA,
THERE IS NO SANTA CLAUS.

40:56.650 --> 40:59.983
* A HAPPY NEW YEAR *

41:01.860 --> 41:05.182
